Genetically engineered Marines travel throughout Space, battling depraved heretics, dishonourable traitors, and vile aliens.

This set includes 4 powered gauntlets, two holding the torn off heads of two different types of alien beast - a brutal ork, and a sinister soulstealer. The third holds a retro style space beaky helmet, and the fourth is empty, perhaps for you to add in your own head model! All four have supported versions.

This is an updated version of the first thing I ever tried to 'sculpt', as opposed to arrange geometric shapes - an ork head. It's a little reflection on my part, comparing where I started to where I am. It's been a slow process, as I take what digital hobby time I can in between physical modelling and all my other fickle interests! But it's still nice to see what I feel in some improvement.

You can see the original here:
https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/power-gauntlet-prime-scale-powered-gauntlet-holding-head

I am an amateur enthusiast 3D designer, and appreciate all constructive feedback. Please check out my other designs for more wargame models, and please consider following me, posting a make, or even leaving a donation via my profile!

**These are proxy models for an existing game system and are not intended for use as permanent replacements for their legitimate game model counterparts.**

These holy ladies march into battle with shield and halberd, ready to purge heretics with bolter and blade.

There are **five** different poses, both with a helmeted and non-helmeted variant. There are also four backpacks, however, they are all identical with the exception of purity seals, so you may use any backpack with any Sister.

Now also included: Sisters 1-5 A pre-supported
Also included: Sisters 1-5B with maces, a remix of mine by another and lost to the void.

If you have any questions, shoot me an email!

Also, **For Printing:** Just rotate the model back (typically 45 degrees) and add auto-supports using light supports. I did mine at 50% density because I love supports, and I have had no print issues. One spot to look out for is the magazine on the bolt pistol, however. I found that it was not supported on Sacresant 1 during my test print and the bottom of the magazine was warped slightly.

Lastly, big thanks to:
 -Jimsbeanz who's armor designs were the base of the torsos and legs.
-Oldgez who released shield designs just in time to save me the trouble of making them myself.
